      "date": "2014-09-10 04:44:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\n>> There may be some patches still using the old style dt_object_xxx() functions, and others, they may be not aware of your patch. So if there can be some mechanism to prevent the old using style, that will be helpful. Rename the functions?\n> I don't understand. Do you mean lu_object_is_dying()? In this case we have changed the type of the parameter from struct lu_object_header * to struct lu_object *.\n\nI mean that you have changed the \"dt_object_exists()\" to return \"bool\", but others maybe not aware of your changes, and their patches maybe still use the code like \"if (dt_object_exists(o) != 0)\". Similar for other functions which return values have been changed from \"int\" to \"bool\".",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
