      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "1a75503e7c84da99dcf887c5e09d95fba2bdc4af",
            "subject": "LU-5408 fid: cleanup fid_is_*() names and uses"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "John L. Hammond",
          "email": "john.hammond@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-08-10 18:46:53.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "John L. Hammond",
          "email": "john.hammond@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-09-05 15:22:51.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "subject": "LU-5470 lu: cleanup some lu_object functions",
        "message": "LU-5470 lu: cleanup some lu_object functions\n\nConvert lu_object_{exists,remote}() from macros to static inline\nfunctions. Change the return type of\n{dt,mdd,mdt}_object_{exists,remote}() from int to bool. Do the same\nfor several MDD object predicates.\n\nRename LU_OBJECT_HEARD_BANSHEE to the less cryptic LU_OBJECT_IS_DYING.\nIn lu_object_is_dying() take a pointer to struct lu_object rather than\nto struct lu_object_header. Add lu_object_kill() to set\nLU_OBJECT_IS_DYING and use it. Add dt_object_is_dying() and\ndt_object_kill(). Remove lfsck_is_dead_obj() and use\ndt_object_is_dying() instead.\n\nReplace expressions of the form lu_object_exists(o) != 0 and\nlu_object_exists(o) == 0 with lu_object_exists(o) and\n!lu_object_exists(o).\n\nSigned-off-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I24b0505fb1c265f859c7b114ff383d0a6f7f6239\n"
      },
